00:00:12.400 --> 00:00:18.848 align:middle line:90%


00:00:18.848 --> 00:00:21.020 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA MEREDITH: Like
many people on this show,

00:00:21.020 --> 00:00:23.240 align:middle line:10%
Suzanne Giesemann was
minding her own business

00:00:23.240 --> 00:00:27.240 align:middle line:10%
as a high-powered navy commander
when life threw her a curveball.

00:00:27.240 --> 00:00:30.400 align:middle line:10%
Deeply prone to strategic
and fact-based thinking,

00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:33.960 align:middle line:10%
her journey may sound familiar
to the rational and logical

00:00:33.960 --> 00:00:37.220 align:middle line:10%
among us, which I think is all
of us, so let's dig into it.

00:00:37.220 --> 00:00:40.660 align:middle line:84%
But before we do, you can see
we have another person here.

00:00:40.660 --> 00:00:42.700 align:middle line:84%
Many of you may
know Emilio Ortiz.

00:00:42.700 --> 00:00:44.880 align:middle line:84%
He has his own podcast
called Just Tap

00:00:44.880 --> 00:00:46.680 align:middle line:90%
In for the last few years.

00:00:46.680 --> 00:00:49.060 align:middle line:90%
A magnificent young man.

00:00:49.060 --> 00:00:51.320 align:middle line:84%
He and I are in
amazing resonance.

00:00:51.320 --> 00:00:52.940 align:middle line:10%
And we want to do
some things together

00:00:52.940 --> 00:00:56.520 align:middle line:10%
so we decided to bring him in
and then try this little kind

00:00:56.520 --> 00:00:58.470 align:middle line:10%
of fun show experiment today.

00:00:58.470 --> 00:00:59.270 align:middle line:10%
Welcome, Emilio.

00:00:59.270 --> 00:01:00.560 align:middle line:10%
>> EMILIO ORTIZ: Thank
you for having me.

00:01:00.560 --> 00:01:01.250 align:middle line:10%
Super excited.

00:01:01.250 --> 00:01:03.417 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: It just feels
so natural having you here.

00:01:03.417 --> 00:01:04.990 align:middle line:90%
>> ORTIZ: Yeah, very natural.

00:01:04.990 --> 00:01:07.780 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So, Suzanne, now
you have all of our attention.

00:01:07.780 --> 00:01:09.600 align:middle line:84%
And you have a
fascinating story.

00:01:09.600 --> 00:01:11.980 align:middle line:84%
I think people love this
story because they can relate

00:01:11.980 --> 00:01:16.820 align:middle line:84%
to the fact that, wow, this
woman had nothing to do with

00:01:16.820 --> 00:01:19.780 align:middle line:84%
the subjects that we're talking
about, mediumship, anything,

00:01:19.780 --> 00:01:20.580 align:middle line:90%
quote, "woo woo."

00:01:20.580 --> 00:01:21.642 align:middle line:90%
That was not your gig.

00:01:21.642 --> 00:01:22.600 align:middle line:10%
You were not religious.

00:01:22.600 --> 00:01:23.920 align:middle line:10%
You were not spiritual.

00:01:23.920 --> 00:01:25.420 align:middle line:84%
Tell us a little
bit about your life

00:01:25.420 --> 00:01:27.780 align:middle line:90%
as a commanding naval officer.

00:01:27.780 --> 00:01:30.285 align:middle line:84%
And also you're an aide to
the Joint Chiefs of Staff?

00:01:30.285 --> 00:01:31.660 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you moved
up there, girl.

00:01:31.660 --> 00:01:34.660 align:middle line:10%
>> SUZANNE GIESEMANN: I was
the personal assistant asked

00:01:34.660 --> 00:01:37.120 align:middle line:10%
by the chairman of the
Joint Chiefs to be his aide.

00:01:37.120 --> 00:01:39.960 align:middle line:10%
He's the head of the whole
United States Armed forces.

00:01:39.960 --> 00:01:43.712 align:middle line:10%
He saw my work and he
said, I need a good aide.

00:01:43.712 --> 00:01:44.920 align:middle line:10%
Would you like to be my aide?

00:01:44.920 --> 00:01:47.320 align:middle line:10%
And when he asked me
that, I thought, would I?

00:01:47.320 --> 00:01:48.960 align:middle line:10%
I mean, I knew
what that entailed.

00:01:48.960 --> 00:01:52.140 align:middle line:84%
You're right there when he meets
kings and queens and other world

00:01:52.140 --> 00:01:55.680 align:middle line:84%
leaders, you fly around
the world on Air Force One.

00:01:55.680 --> 00:01:59.910 align:middle line:84%
And I think it was because I was
so left brained and very logical

00:01:59.910 --> 00:02:00.810 align:middle line:90%
and very analytical.

00:02:00.810 --> 00:02:02.970 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: OK, let's talk
a little bit about that.

00:02:02.970 --> 00:02:04.930 align:middle line:84%
What's it like flying
on Air Force One?

00:02:04.930 --> 00:02:07.080 align:middle line:84%
And then we'll get to the Queen
Elizabeth story in a minute.

00:02:07.080 --> 00:02:09.530 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: I tell people
it's like the old show Get Smart

00:02:09.530 --> 00:02:11.630 align:middle line:84%
where there are multiple doors
at the beginning of the show

00:02:11.630 --> 00:02:12.350 align:middle line:90%
that open.

00:02:12.350 --> 00:02:14.308 align:middle line:84%
As you go up the stairs
to get on Air Force One

00:02:14.308 --> 00:02:16.690 align:middle line:84%
and one set of doors opens,
there's another set of doors.

00:02:16.690 --> 00:02:18.010 align:middle line:84%
And then there's
a conference room,

00:02:18.010 --> 00:02:20.427 align:middle line:84%
and that's where I was with
just the chairman of the Joint

00:02:20.427 --> 00:02:22.610 align:middle line:84%
Chiefs, the Secretary of
Defense and his assistant.

00:02:22.610 --> 00:02:23.550 align:middle line:90%
The four of us.

00:02:23.550 --> 00:02:25.630 align:middle line:84%
And then the plane
takes off and in

00:02:25.630 --> 00:02:27.610 align:middle line:84%
walks the president
at an angle because--

00:02:27.610 --> 00:02:29.360 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Which
president are we talking?

00:02:29.360 --> 00:02:30.930 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: President
Bush, the younger one.

00:02:30.930 --> 00:02:33.143 align:middle line:84%
And it was his first flight
on Air Force One as well.

00:02:33.143 --> 00:02:34.060 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Oh, really?

00:02:34.060 --> 00:02:34.860 align:middle line:90%
>> GIESEMANN: Yeah.

00:02:34.860 --> 00:02:37.640 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: OK, let's talk
about Queen Elizabeth and what

00:02:37.640 --> 00:02:38.440 align:middle line:90%
happened.

00:02:38.440 --> 00:02:41.670 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: Well, I was very
excited because my boss had been

00:02:41.670 --> 00:02:44.490 align:middle line:84%
chosen to be knighted
by Queen Elizabeth.

00:02:44.490 --> 00:02:47.190 align:middle line:84%
We were three hours
out over the Atlantic,

00:02:47.190 --> 00:02:51.270 align:middle line:84%
and we got a call that a small
plane had flown into the World

00:02:51.270 --> 00:02:52.910 align:middle line:90%
Trade Center towers.

00:02:52.910 --> 00:02:56.130 align:middle line:84%
And so we put on the headsets,
and were just witness

00:02:56.130 --> 00:02:57.310 align:middle line:90%
to the reports.

00:02:57.310 --> 00:02:59.947 align:middle line:84%
And then I called back to
the Pentagon to our office,

00:02:59.947 --> 00:03:01.030 align:middle line:90%
was speaking to a colonel.

00:03:01.030 --> 00:03:03.155 align:middle line:84%
And he said, Suzanne,
something just happened here.

00:03:03.155 --> 00:03:03.970 align:middle line:90%
I have to go.

00:03:03.970 --> 00:03:06.977 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, that's
when the jet hit.

00:03:06.977 --> 00:03:09.060 align:middle line:84%
So we turned around, didn't
get to meet the Queen.

00:03:09.060 --> 00:03:11.390 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And you saw
the wreckage afterwards?

00:03:11.390 --> 00:03:13.390 align:middle line:10%
>> GIESEMANN: First we
got back to the Pentagon,

00:03:13.390 --> 00:03:16.490 align:middle line:10%
and the Chairman immediately had
a briefing from his terrorism

00:03:16.490 --> 00:03:19.030 align:middle line:10%
experts and then said, I want
to see the site of the impact.

00:03:19.030 --> 00:03:21.030 align:middle line:84%
And we started going through
the center of the building.

00:03:21.030 --> 00:03:23.030 align:middle line:84%
The lights are out,
it's filled with smoke.

00:03:23.030 --> 00:03:26.450 align:middle line:84%
So we went out into this bright
sunshine around the corner,

00:03:26.450 --> 00:03:30.070 align:middle line:84%
and there's just this
gaping hole in the building,

00:03:30.070 --> 00:03:33.330 align:middle line:84%
the firemen are spraying
it, it's clearly collapsed.

00:03:33.330 --> 00:03:35.630 align:middle line:84%
Ambulances lined
up along the curb.

00:03:35.630 --> 00:03:38.950 align:middle line:84%
I stepped over jet engine
pieces in the grass.

00:03:38.950 --> 00:03:42.190 align:middle line:84%
There was no doubt in my mind
that this had been a jet.

00:03:42.190 --> 00:03:44.190 align:middle line:90%
You could identify the blades.

00:03:44.190 --> 00:03:46.030 align:middle line:84%
There was a commander,
same rank as I am,

00:03:46.030 --> 00:03:49.290 align:middle line:84%
that was two weeks away from
retirement who was killed.

00:03:49.290 --> 00:03:51.790 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't eligible to
retire for two more years,

00:03:51.790 --> 00:03:52.970 align:middle line:90%
but I put in my papers.

00:03:52.970 --> 00:03:55.870 align:middle line:84%
And on the very day that
I was retirement eligible,

00:03:55.870 --> 00:03:58.730 align:middle line:84%
I retired and the next day
we set off in our sailboat.

00:03:58.730 --> 00:04:01.790 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And you were sailing,
and you were off the Coast

00:04:01.790 --> 00:04:06.110 align:middle line:84%
of Croatia and then another
horrifying thing happened.

00:04:06.110 --> 00:04:08.030 align:middle line:84%
And then from this
point, we're going

00:04:08.030 --> 00:04:10.890 align:middle line:84%
to start talking about how
you became who you are today.

00:04:10.890 --> 00:04:12.930 align:middle line:84%
Emilio's going to
jump in a minute.

00:04:12.930 --> 00:04:14.850 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about
what happened.

00:04:14.850 --> 00:04:18.470 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: We were not able
to access email or phone calls

00:04:18.470 --> 00:04:19.649 align:middle line:90%
in 2006.

00:04:19.649 --> 00:04:21.850 align:middle line:84%
We got them over a
single sideband radio.

00:04:21.850 --> 00:04:24.310 align:middle line:84%
Really great technology
at the time, but very

00:04:24.310 --> 00:04:26.130 align:middle line:90%
challenging to get emails.

00:04:26.130 --> 00:04:28.710 align:middle line:84%
And we got one from my
stepdaughter, Elizabeth, that

00:04:28.710 --> 00:04:31.310 align:middle line:90%
said, you need to call home.

00:04:31.310 --> 00:04:32.410 align:middle line:90%
It's important.

00:04:32.410 --> 00:04:33.250 align:middle line:90%
That's all it said.

00:04:33.250 --> 00:04:35.490 align:middle line:84%
And I had no psychic
abilities at the time,

00:04:35.490 --> 00:04:37.490 align:middle line:84%
did not suspect
anything was wrong.

00:04:37.490 --> 00:04:42.050 align:middle line:84%
But we were on a remote
island, we had no phone,

00:04:42.050 --> 00:04:45.590 align:middle line:84%
so we had to spend a day
getting to the nearest phone.

00:04:45.590 --> 00:04:48.350 align:middle line:84%
And my husband
dialed his daughter,

00:04:48.350 --> 00:04:52.470 align:middle line:84%
and my other stepdaughter's
husband answered the phone.

00:04:52.470 --> 00:04:55.450 align:middle line:84%
Tye, my husband, was very
pleasant, hey, what's up?

00:04:55.450 --> 00:05:00.010 align:middle line:84%
And my son-in-law
said, nothing good.

00:05:00.010 --> 00:05:03.010 align:middle line:10%
And all of a sudden I
thought-- well, Susan

00:05:03.010 --> 00:05:05.630 align:middle line:10%
had been six months
pregnant, and I thought, oh,

00:05:05.630 --> 00:05:07.850 align:middle line:10%
she lost the baby.

00:05:07.850 --> 00:05:09.970 align:middle line:10%
It was so much worse.

00:05:09.970 --> 00:05:12.770 align:middle line:10%
I saw my husband crumple
against the phone booth.

00:05:12.770 --> 00:05:19.210 align:middle line:10%
And he looked at me and
he said, Susan is gone.

00:05:19.210 --> 00:05:22.130 align:middle line:90%
It was incomprehensible.

00:05:22.130 --> 00:05:25.290 align:middle line:84%
She was absolutely
the light of his life.

00:05:25.290 --> 00:05:28.445 align:middle line:84%
And so it was the baby
and Susan were gone.

00:05:28.445 --> 00:05:30.570 align:middle line:84%
So we suddenly had to get
back to the United States

00:05:30.570 --> 00:05:32.230 align:middle line:90%
with our dog, leave the boat.

00:05:32.230 --> 00:05:35.570 align:middle line:90%
It was a personal nightmare.

00:05:35.570 --> 00:05:39.370 align:middle line:84%
9/11 was feeling everybody's
grief but being able to stay

00:05:39.370 --> 00:05:43.590 align:middle line:84%
beyond it, now suddenly we were
immersed in grief of our own.

00:05:43.590 --> 00:05:48.010 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And it's important
to point out that by a stroke

00:05:48.010 --> 00:05:52.507 align:middle line:84%
of whatever, she was literally
struck by lightning and died.

00:05:52.507 --> 00:05:53.340 align:middle line:90%
>> GIESEMANN: Right.

00:05:53.340 --> 00:05:55.780 align:middle line:84%
She was struck by lightning
crossing the flight line

00:05:55.780 --> 00:05:56.580 align:middle line:90%
at work.

00:05:56.580 --> 00:06:00.300 align:middle line:84%
She was a marine sergeant,
another military member.

00:06:00.300 --> 00:06:03.700 align:middle line:90%
And it was not even raining.

00:06:03.700 --> 00:06:07.400 align:middle line:84%
The bolt of lightning came out
of the blue and struck her.

00:06:07.400 --> 00:06:11.140 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And this will come
up as very important later on.

00:06:11.140 --> 00:06:13.750 align:middle line:90%
So, Emilio, take it from here.

00:06:13.750 --> 00:06:18.240 align:middle line:10%
>> ORTIZ: Yeah, it's a
very chilling experience.

00:06:18.240 --> 00:06:22.240 align:middle line:10%
And when you went back to go
see her and you saw the body,

00:06:22.240 --> 00:06:24.140 align:middle line:10%
you said, this isn't Susan.

00:06:24.140 --> 00:06:26.380 align:middle line:84%
And what's interesting
is that you were reading

00:06:26.380 --> 00:06:31.200 align:middle line:84%
a book about mediumship on the
boat, Crossing the Atlantic,

00:06:31.200 --> 00:06:33.840 align:middle line:84%
and you made this
commitment to yourself,

00:06:33.840 --> 00:06:36.180 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to connect with Susan.

00:06:36.180 --> 00:06:39.980 align:middle line:84%
And I found a little recipe
of how you started opening up.

00:06:39.980 --> 00:06:41.780 align:middle line:84%
And I would love to
hear your take, which

00:06:41.780 --> 00:06:45.860 align:middle line:84%
is what's possible for you and
for people when they connect

00:06:45.860 --> 00:06:50.080 align:middle line:84%
with unconditional love,
devotional intention

00:06:50.080 --> 00:06:54.680 align:middle line:84%
and this military grade type
of devotion and discipline

00:06:54.680 --> 00:06:57.440 align:middle line:84%
to be able to open and pierce
the veil to the other side

00:06:57.440 --> 00:06:59.460 align:middle line:84%
and connect with Susan
for the first time.

00:06:59.460 --> 00:07:02.640 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: Well, Emilio, you
nailed it right there because it

00:07:02.640 --> 00:07:06.100 align:middle line:84%
was this knowing within me
that she could not be gone.

00:07:06.100 --> 00:07:08.320 align:middle line:84%
And I know that it's no
coincidence that I just

00:07:08.320 --> 00:07:10.880 align:middle line:84%
happened to find a book about
mediumship when we sailed

00:07:10.880 --> 00:07:14.140 align:middle line:84%
past the US Navy base in Italy,
and there was a grab bag fill it

00:07:14.140 --> 00:07:14.940 align:middle line:90%
with books.

00:07:14.940 --> 00:07:17.700 align:middle line:10%
And there's this book by
James Van Praagh, a medium.

00:07:17.700 --> 00:07:19.380 align:middle line:84%
I had not studied
mediumship at all.

00:07:19.380 --> 00:07:20.640 align:middle line:90%
That sounds interesting.

00:07:20.640 --> 00:07:22.400 align:middle line:84%
And I thought it
was nonsense when

00:07:22.400 --> 00:07:24.440 align:middle line:84%
I read what he wrote
about a greater reality

00:07:24.440 --> 00:07:26.700 align:middle line:84%
where people are still
living and working.

00:07:26.700 --> 00:07:28.700 align:middle line:84%
And I hid the book
from my husband.

00:07:28.700 --> 00:07:29.820 align:middle line:90%
In fact, I threw it out.

00:07:29.820 --> 00:07:31.760 align:middle line:84%
James knows this
so I can say that.

00:07:31.760 --> 00:07:34.580 align:middle line:84%
Because I didn't want him
seeing me reading this book.

00:07:34.580 --> 00:07:37.680 align:middle line:84%
But now I see that it
opened me to possibilities,

00:07:37.680 --> 00:07:38.940 align:middle line:90%
and that is key.

00:07:38.940 --> 00:07:42.720 align:middle line:84%
If our minds are not
open, open minds,

00:07:42.720 --> 00:07:44.780 align:middle line:90%
we won't even explore something.

00:07:44.780 --> 00:07:48.820 align:middle line:84%
But looking at Susan's body, I
just knew that what James said

00:07:48.820 --> 00:07:51.300 align:middle line:90%
was right that we have to go on.

00:07:51.300 --> 00:07:52.560 align:middle line:90%
So that's right.

00:07:52.560 --> 00:07:55.280 align:middle line:84%
That's where the military
discipline kicked in,

00:07:55.280 --> 00:07:57.760 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to connect with
her no matter what it takes.

00:07:57.760 --> 00:08:00.220 align:middle line:84%
But today I realize,
after people come up to me

00:08:00.220 --> 00:08:02.380 align:middle line:84%
and they say, yeah,
but you have discipline

00:08:02.380 --> 00:08:05.080 align:middle line:84%
and I don't, it's not
so much discipline.

00:08:05.080 --> 00:08:06.820 align:middle line:90%
It's commitment.

00:08:06.820 --> 00:08:10.600 align:middle line:84%
And when your heart knows
something, you commit to it.

00:08:10.600 --> 00:08:13.260 align:middle line:84%
And when you love someone with
all your heart and your heart

00:08:13.260 --> 00:08:16.140 align:middle line:84%
and your soul knows
they're still here,

00:08:16.140 --> 00:08:19.060 align:middle line:84%
you're just not going to stop
until you make that connection.

00:08:19.060 --> 00:08:21.940 align:middle line:84%
And that opens us up
to this connection

00:08:21.940 --> 00:08:23.760 align:middle line:90%
that's available for all of us.

00:08:23.760 --> 00:08:24.560 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:08:24.560 --> 00:08:26.740 align:middle line:84%
So let's get into
the-- a little bit

00:08:26.740 --> 00:08:28.700 align:middle line:84%
of the nuts and bolts
of when you first

00:08:28.700 --> 00:08:30.980 align:middle line:84%
started feeling that
transmission where

00:08:30.980 --> 00:08:32.700 align:middle line:84%
you started feeling
the connection that's

00:08:32.700 --> 00:08:33.778 align:middle line:90%
called mediumship.

00:08:33.778 --> 00:08:36.159 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: I had no idea
it was going to be a medium.

00:08:36.159 --> 00:08:38.880 align:middle line:84%
All I wanted to do was
feel Susan's presence,

00:08:38.880 --> 00:08:40.820 align:middle line:90%
to know that she was around.

00:08:40.820 --> 00:08:44.100 align:middle line:84%
And Regina, she came to me
a few years ago and told me

00:08:44.100 --> 00:08:48.280 align:middle line:84%
she deliberately held
back for three years so

00:08:48.280 --> 00:08:52.360 align:middle line:84%
that I would open up to
other people and other beings

00:08:52.360 --> 00:08:56.240 align:middle line:84%
and the greater reality, and
have far more experiences

00:08:56.240 --> 00:08:58.080 align:middle line:84%
with expanded states
of consciousness

00:08:58.080 --> 00:09:00.640 align:middle line:84%
than if I had sensed
her right away.

00:09:00.640 --> 00:09:02.560 align:middle line:84%
So it's very
important that people

00:09:02.560 --> 00:09:05.500 align:middle line:84%
understand that there's no
timeline to how long this takes.

00:09:05.500 --> 00:09:09.400 align:middle line:84%
It's really what your
soul needs to evolve.

00:09:09.400 --> 00:09:14.600 align:middle line:84%
But in the process of every day
sitting quietly and shutting out

00:09:14.600 --> 00:09:17.280 align:middle line:84%
the outer world and saying,
Susan, where are you?

00:09:17.280 --> 00:09:20.520 align:middle line:84%
Susan, let me see you, let
me hear you, let me feel you,

00:09:20.520 --> 00:09:23.840 align:middle line:84%
I had adventures that
I never expected.

00:09:23.840 --> 00:09:29.060 align:middle line:84%
And started to connect with
guides and get evidence.

00:09:29.060 --> 00:09:31.680 align:middle line:84%
And, happily, I had a
reading with another medium

00:09:31.680 --> 00:09:33.380 align:middle line:84%
and then learned
what's possible,

00:09:33.380 --> 00:09:35.820 align:middle line:84%
learned why getting
evidence is important.

00:09:35.820 --> 00:09:39.220 align:middle line:84%
So I started questioning those
who I sensed, prove this to me

00:09:39.220 --> 00:09:41.240 align:middle line:84%
this is who you are,
and it just opened up

00:09:41.240 --> 00:09:44.400 align:middle line:84%
this whole other avenue
that I never expected.

00:09:44.400 --> 00:09:47.810 align:middle line:84%
>> ORTIZ: I would love to know,
after those three years when

00:09:47.810 --> 00:09:51.250 align:middle line:84%
Susan came to you, what did
she explain to you that she was

00:09:51.250 --> 00:09:53.496 align:middle line:90%
doing on the other side?

00:09:53.496 --> 00:09:55.882 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: Wow,
did I even ask you?

00:09:55.882 --> 00:09:57.340 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Then
you are saying you.

00:09:57.340 --> 00:09:58.750 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: Yeah,
because she's right here.

00:09:58.750 --> 00:10:00.076 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah, I assume.

00:10:00.076 --> 00:10:00.876 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:10:00.876 --> 00:10:03.390 align:middle line:10%
>> GIESEMANN: She didn't
tell me what she was doing.

00:10:03.390 --> 00:10:06.210 align:middle line:84%
She just wanted her dad
to know that she was fine.

00:10:06.210 --> 00:10:09.010 align:middle line:84%
I was her messenger,
which is what a medium is.

00:10:09.010 --> 00:10:10.670 align:middle line:90%
And I could tell she was fine.

00:10:10.670 --> 00:10:14.330 align:middle line:84%
And now she helps
me, not all the time.

00:10:14.330 --> 00:10:18.050 align:middle line:84%
But I have never really
asked her what she was doing.

00:10:18.050 --> 00:10:19.500 align:middle line:90%
She just said just hanging out.

00:10:19.500 --> 00:10:20.960 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Just hanging
out, waiting for you.

00:10:20.960 --> 00:10:22.320 align:middle line:90%
>> ORTIZ: Having a good time.

00:10:22.320 --> 00:10:24.970 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So this talk
about one of the things--

00:10:24.970 --> 00:10:27.250 align:middle line:84%
because people
doubt themselves--

00:10:27.250 --> 00:10:31.130 align:middle line:84%
so in this process of
opening up and being

00:10:31.130 --> 00:10:33.850 align:middle line:84%
comfortable with the notion we
might be speaking to entities

00:10:33.850 --> 00:10:39.690 align:middle line:84%
beyond ourselves, tell us how
you differentiated between other

00:10:39.690 --> 00:10:43.110 align:middle line:84%
and what was your own mind
or your own higher mind.

00:10:43.110 --> 00:10:44.740 align:middle line:84%
What was the
differentiating factor?

00:10:44.740 --> 00:10:47.282 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: That is the number
one challenge for people who

00:10:47.282 --> 00:10:48.410 align:middle line:90%
connect, am I making it up.

00:10:48.410 --> 00:10:49.650 align:middle line:90%
It's twofold.

00:10:49.650 --> 00:10:51.710 align:middle line:84%
There's a knowing in
the heart that this

00:10:51.710 --> 00:10:54.950 align:middle line:84%
is something beyond
what I call me,

00:10:54.950 --> 00:10:59.750 align:middle line:84%
and it's receiving insights
or information that stand out,

00:10:59.750 --> 00:11:02.270 align:middle line:84%
that are not what
you expected to hear,

00:11:02.270 --> 00:11:05.670 align:middle line:90%
that are helpful, not ordinary.

00:11:05.670 --> 00:11:08.450 align:middle line:84%
So you look for
something that, oh,

00:11:08.450 --> 00:11:09.980 align:middle line:90%
I wouldn't have thought of that.

00:11:09.980 --> 00:11:12.480 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: It has to be apart
from your own thought process.

00:11:12.480 --> 00:11:13.890 align:middle line:90%
>> GIESEMANN: Not always.

00:11:13.890 --> 00:11:17.330 align:middle line:84%
There are things that we need
to hear that we might think,

00:11:17.330 --> 00:11:18.950 align:middle line:90%
but why did it come up now?

00:11:18.950 --> 00:11:19.750 align:middle line:90%
So the timing is--

00:11:19.750 --> 00:11:20.810 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: So timing too.

00:11:20.810 --> 00:11:20.956 align:middle line:90%
>> GIESEMANN: Mhm.

00:11:20.956 --> 00:11:22.130 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK, interesting.

00:11:22.130 --> 00:11:26.030 align:middle line:84%
Well, all right, so this
gets us toward something

00:11:26.030 --> 00:11:28.870 align:middle line:84%
we both-- we all
love is the story

00:11:28.870 --> 00:11:32.430 align:middle line:84%
that really touched your
heart and brought you deeper

00:11:32.430 --> 00:11:36.470 align:middle line:84%
into it, which is the story
of a young man named Wolf.

00:11:36.470 --> 00:11:37.570 align:middle line:90%
>> ORTIZ: Yeah.

00:11:37.570 --> 00:11:40.130 align:middle line:84%
Wolf, I mean, being
also a young man

00:11:40.130 --> 00:11:43.530 align:middle line:84%
and he passed in a very
similar way as Susan,

00:11:43.530 --> 00:11:48.890 align:middle line:84%
with a bolt of lightning, he was
a very peculiar young man where

00:11:48.890 --> 00:11:51.010 align:middle line:84%
he had pictures-- and
maybe we can pull one up--

00:11:51.010 --> 00:11:53.750 align:middle line:84%
where he was pointing
at his head and saying,

00:11:53.750 --> 00:11:56.090 align:middle line:90%
I was in two worlds at once.

00:11:56.090 --> 00:11:58.090 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't shut off the voices.

00:11:58.090 --> 00:11:59.990 align:middle line:84%
He was diagnosed
as schizophrenic.

00:11:59.990 --> 00:12:02.490 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's
a powerful reframe

00:12:02.490 --> 00:12:07.770 align:middle line:84%
to telling how extraordinary
of a being he was

00:12:07.770 --> 00:12:12.310 align:middle line:84%
and how can the society just
say you have a mental illness.

00:12:12.310 --> 00:12:14.890 align:middle line:84%
So what was your
experience like of getting

00:12:14.890 --> 00:12:17.570 align:middle line:84%
to know a spirit that
was on the other side,

00:12:17.570 --> 00:12:21.180 align:middle line:84%
and also dealing with these
things in the physical realm?

00:12:21.180 --> 00:12:24.290 align:middle line:10%
>> GIESEMANN: The importance
of telling Wolf's story is that

00:12:24.290 --> 00:12:26.230 align:middle line:10%
of all the souls
I've connected with,

00:12:26.230 --> 00:12:29.550 align:middle line:10%
he left for all of
us the most profound,

00:12:29.550 --> 00:12:32.510 align:middle line:10%
irrefutable evidence
that we are souls.

00:12:32.510 --> 00:12:34.350 align:middle line:84%
This is why we focus
on Wolf's story,

00:12:34.350 --> 00:12:37.030 align:middle line:84%
because he knew he would
be struck by lightning.

00:12:37.030 --> 00:12:39.550 align:middle line:84%
He left a poem about
it, and he left

00:12:39.550 --> 00:12:42.110 align:middle line:84%
a drawing that shows
where it would happen

00:12:42.110 --> 00:12:43.990 align:middle line:84%
and what would
happen afterwards.

00:12:43.990 --> 00:12:46.710 align:middle line:84%
And then he came through
to me after connecting me

00:12:46.710 --> 00:12:49.350 align:middle line:84%
with his dad and his
stepmom, Mike and Beth.

00:12:49.350 --> 00:12:51.510 align:middle line:84%
And dropped in on
me unexpectedly

00:12:51.510 --> 00:12:53.690 align:middle line:84%
when there was nobody
to give me feedback--

00:12:53.690 --> 00:12:55.550 align:middle line:84%
I'm thinking I'm
reading their mind--

00:12:55.550 --> 00:12:58.390 align:middle line:84%
and told me all about
himself, and left out

00:12:58.390 --> 00:13:02.470 align:middle line:84%
a few details that helped me
to unravel this mystery of why

00:13:02.470 --> 00:13:03.910 align:middle line:90%
Wolf came back.

00:13:03.910 --> 00:13:07.110 align:middle line:84%
To find out, after doing a
reading for his parents, that he

00:13:07.110 --> 00:13:10.242 align:middle line:84%
was diagnosed as
mentally ill stunned me

00:13:10.242 --> 00:13:11.450 align:middle line:90%
in the middle of the reading.

00:13:11.450 --> 00:13:14.038 align:middle line:84%
I remember saying--
well, first of all,

00:13:14.038 --> 00:13:15.830 align:middle line:84%
I was stuttering and
shaking in the reading

00:13:15.830 --> 00:13:16.980 align:middle line:90%
because he was so powerful.

00:13:16.980 --> 00:13:18.910 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: You have
a documentary on him.

00:13:18.910 --> 00:13:20.823 align:middle line:84%
And you hear you
doing the reading,

00:13:20.823 --> 00:13:22.240 align:middle line:84%
and you're stuttering
and shaking.

00:13:22.240 --> 00:13:23.520 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: Yes,
and I'm not a stutter.

00:13:23.520 --> 00:13:25.630 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And you
said it's because soul,

00:13:25.630 --> 00:13:28.170 align:middle line:84%
you never encountered
such a powerful soul,

00:13:28.170 --> 00:13:29.850 align:middle line:90%
that energy coming through you.

00:13:29.850 --> 00:13:31.120 align:middle line:90%
So continue, yeah.

00:13:31.120 --> 00:13:34.870 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: And so here's this
powerful soul who was so loving.

00:13:34.870 --> 00:13:38.880 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly I said, he
just said schizophrenia.

00:13:38.880 --> 00:13:40.200 align:middle line:90%
That doesn't make sense.

00:13:40.200 --> 00:13:42.160 align:middle line:84%
And his stepmother
said, oh, yeah, he

00:13:42.160 --> 00:13:44.320 align:middle line:90%
was diagnosed schizophrenic.

00:13:44.320 --> 00:13:46.880 align:middle line:84%
And it just knocked
me off balance

00:13:46.880 --> 00:13:48.600 align:middle line:90%
because he was so powerful.

00:13:48.600 --> 00:13:52.200 align:middle line:84%
And that's when he said, I
was in two worlds at once.

00:13:52.200 --> 00:13:53.660 align:middle line:90%
It was very busy in here.

00:13:53.660 --> 00:13:56.120 align:middle line:84%
And his dad said,
he always said that.

00:13:56.120 --> 00:13:58.860 align:middle line:84%
And they have a picture
of him doing that.

00:13:58.860 --> 00:14:02.840 align:middle line:84%
And to your point, Emilio,
that is such a powerful piece

00:14:02.840 --> 00:14:04.720 align:middle line:84%
of this documentary
because we all

00:14:04.720 --> 00:14:08.040 align:middle line:84%
know people who are
different, who don't fit in.

00:14:08.040 --> 00:14:12.240 align:middle line:84%
And this film is helping
people see them differently,

00:14:12.240 --> 00:14:14.460 align:middle line:90%
to see the souls in all of us.

00:14:14.460 --> 00:14:16.400 align:middle line:84%
If we could walk
around and instead

00:14:16.400 --> 00:14:18.960 align:middle line:84%
of saying, oh, they're
weird, oh, they're strange

00:14:18.960 --> 00:14:23.900 align:middle line:84%
and push back, say, mm,
but their soul is fine,

00:14:23.900 --> 00:14:26.142 align:middle line:84%
let me see if I can
connect with their soul,

00:14:26.142 --> 00:14:27.850 align:middle line:84%
it would be a completely
different world.

00:14:27.850 --> 00:14:31.980 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I want to get deeper
into that topic in a little bit

00:14:31.980 --> 00:14:34.760 align:middle line:84%
because so many of the souls
being born now are wired quite

00:14:34.760 --> 00:14:35.680 align:middle line:90%
differently.

00:14:35.680 --> 00:14:38.460 align:middle line:84%
So we need to get into that,
people on the spectrum who

00:14:38.460 --> 00:14:40.900 align:middle line:84%
appear to be on the
spectrum, who are also

00:14:40.900 --> 00:14:42.200 align:middle line:90%
walking in both worlds.

00:14:42.200 --> 00:14:46.220 align:middle line:84%
But some of the cool stuff
about Wolf too because this

00:14:46.220 --> 00:14:48.580 align:middle line:84%
brings back your
daughter, the lightning,

00:14:48.580 --> 00:14:50.100 align:middle line:90%
being struck by lightning.

00:14:50.100 --> 00:14:52.200 align:middle line:90%
Her little dog was named Thor.

00:14:52.200 --> 00:14:54.660 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: Yeah,
the God of lightning.

00:14:54.660 --> 00:14:56.740 align:middle line:90%
Three dogs, Regina.

00:14:56.740 --> 00:14:59.680 align:middle line:84%
I only came to this
awareness a few years ago,

00:14:59.680 --> 00:15:02.740 align:middle line:90%
Thor, the son of Odin.

00:15:02.740 --> 00:15:07.000 align:middle line:84%
Loki was her other dog,
which is Odin's son as well.

00:15:07.000 --> 00:15:10.300 align:middle line:84%
And the other dog was Athena,
who is also associated

00:15:10.300 --> 00:15:11.620 align:middle line:90%
with thunder and lightning.

00:15:11.620 --> 00:15:12.420 align:middle line:90%
And then she--

00:15:12.420 --> 00:15:13.660 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: From
her father, Zeus.

00:15:13.660 --> 00:15:14.720 align:middle line:90%
>> GIESEMANN: Yes, yes.

00:15:14.720 --> 00:15:16.160 align:middle line:90%
And she was killed by lightning.

00:15:16.160 --> 00:15:18.760 align:middle line:84%
That didn't occur to
us until years later.

00:15:18.760 --> 00:15:19.560 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:15:19.560 --> 00:15:21.940 align:middle line:84%
And so that's
really what brought

00:15:21.940 --> 00:15:23.880 align:middle line:90%
you together is his parents.

00:15:23.880 --> 00:15:26.620 align:middle line:84%
You were at the Edgar
Cayce Institute,

00:15:26.620 --> 00:15:28.240 align:middle line:84%
and you were doing
a lecture there.

00:15:28.240 --> 00:15:30.900 align:middle line:84%
And the parents heard you
talk about your daughter being

00:15:30.900 --> 00:15:32.720 align:middle line:84%
struck by lightning,
and they just came up.

00:15:32.720 --> 00:15:33.807 align:middle line:90%
They had to talk to you.

00:15:33.807 --> 00:15:35.390 align:middle line:84%
And that's how this
whole thing began.

00:15:35.390 --> 00:15:36.190 align:middle line:90%
>> GIESEMANN: Yes.

00:15:36.190 --> 00:15:39.640 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So let's talk a
little bit more about what was

00:15:39.640 --> 00:15:43.080 align:middle line:84%
in Wolf's room, his
preparation for this,

00:15:43.080 --> 00:15:46.220 align:middle line:84%
the t-shirt he
had on, et cetera.

00:15:46.220 --> 00:15:47.563 align:middle line:90%
Just tell us the whole story.

00:15:47.563 --> 00:15:48.980 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: It's
a real spoiler,

00:15:48.980 --> 00:15:50.190 align:middle line:90%
but there's so much more to it.

00:15:50.190 --> 00:15:52.565 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: There's so much
more to it that people can see

00:15:52.565 --> 00:15:55.580 align:middle line:84%
in the documentary, but just
give us a good dose of it now.

00:15:55.580 --> 00:15:58.520 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: The final poem
that definitely was written

00:15:58.520 --> 00:16:00.300 align:middle line:90%
within two days of his passing--

00:16:00.300 --> 00:16:03.520 align:middle line:84%
because his father visited
him just two days prior--

00:16:03.520 --> 00:16:05.160 align:middle line:84%
and always walked
around his apartment

00:16:05.160 --> 00:16:07.160 align:middle line:84%
to see what new
artwork Wolf had put

00:16:07.160 --> 00:16:10.920 align:middle line:84%
on the walls, which were
covered, floor to ceiling,

00:16:10.920 --> 00:16:12.120 align:middle line:90%
with his artwork--

00:16:12.120 --> 00:16:14.780 align:middle line:84%
which was a little
dark, a little odd

00:16:14.780 --> 00:16:16.560 align:middle line:90%
but that's who he was--

00:16:16.560 --> 00:16:20.500 align:middle line:84%
this poem was not there when
dad visited the apartment.

00:16:20.500 --> 00:16:23.000 align:middle line:84%
And the final line
of the poem says,

00:16:23.000 --> 00:16:29.080 align:middle line:84%
"Time has come for the light
of nature to free my soul."

00:16:29.080 --> 00:16:34.100 align:middle line:84%
He tacked that to the wall, set
a chair that wasn't normally

00:16:34.100 --> 00:16:37.360 align:middle line:84%
in the middle of the
floor, facing that poem

00:16:37.360 --> 00:16:39.860 align:middle line:84%
as if to say, sit
here and read this.

00:16:39.860 --> 00:16:43.820 align:middle line:84%
And then across from the
poem, behind the chair,

00:16:43.820 --> 00:16:47.140 align:middle line:84%
he cut out his favorite
t-shirt that he had just

00:16:47.140 --> 00:16:49.940 align:middle line:84%
worn the weekend
before, and put what

00:16:49.940 --> 00:16:53.300 align:middle line:84%
was on that t-shirt on the
wall, a bolt of lightning.

00:16:53.300 --> 00:16:54.967 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: You can't
make this stuff up.

00:16:54.967 --> 00:16:56.133 align:middle line:90%
>> GIESEMANN: No, you can't.

00:16:56.133 --> 00:16:58.580 align:middle line:84%
>> ORTIZ: It was like an art
gallery where he had a chair

00:16:58.580 --> 00:17:02.800 align:middle line:84%
specifically where he wanted
people to sit, read the poem.

00:17:02.800 --> 00:17:06.380 align:middle line:84%
And in the back he had the
symbology of the lightning.

00:17:06.380 --> 00:17:09.300 align:middle line:84%
And for you, you've had
this thread of lightning

00:17:09.300 --> 00:17:12.940 align:middle line:84%
throughout your whole life,
Susan's passing then Wolf.

00:17:12.940 --> 00:17:15.860 align:middle line:84%
Your group, Sanaya,
actually means--

00:17:15.860 --> 00:17:17.880 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: The name
means flash of lightning.

00:17:17.880 --> 00:17:19.803 align:middle line:84%
They gave that to me
without me knowing it.

00:17:19.803 --> 00:17:21.220 align:middle line:84%
But you just
reminded me, when you

00:17:21.220 --> 00:17:22.980 align:middle line:84%
talked about the
artwork, what we left out

00:17:22.980 --> 00:17:27.440 align:middle line:84%
was there was also a drawing
with his poem that he drew.

00:17:27.440 --> 00:17:31.810 align:middle line:84%
It's an eye which the saying
goes when your eye is single,

00:17:31.810 --> 00:17:33.610 align:middle line:84%
may your entire body
be filled with light.

00:17:33.610 --> 00:17:35.402 align:middle line:84%
That's paraphrasing,
of course, but the eye

00:17:35.402 --> 00:17:37.070 align:middle line:90%
is the window of the soul.

00:17:37.070 --> 00:17:40.710 align:middle line:84%
In the center, the pupil
is the yin yang symbol.

00:17:40.710 --> 00:17:42.670 align:middle line:84%
On the left is a
dreamcatcher, which

00:17:42.670 --> 00:17:45.390 align:middle line:84%
is the perfect symbology
for the web of connections

00:17:45.390 --> 00:17:47.310 align:middle line:90%
that unites us all.

00:17:47.310 --> 00:17:49.190 align:middle line:90%
But on the right--

00:17:49.190 --> 00:17:52.950 align:middle line:84%
his parents didn't realize
it until three weeks later--

00:17:52.950 --> 00:17:56.890 align:middle line:84%
is the tree where he was
struck, the very tree.

00:17:56.890 --> 00:17:59.630 align:middle line:84%
It's very distinctive
big old birch tree.

00:17:59.630 --> 00:18:02.010 align:middle line:84%
But at the base of
it, in his drawing

00:18:02.010 --> 00:18:07.390 align:middle line:84%
you can see two roses that his
parents put there in tribute

00:18:07.390 --> 00:18:09.830 align:middle line:90%
to him after he was killed.

00:18:09.830 --> 00:18:12.690 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And not only
that, when they went in, neat

00:18:12.690 --> 00:18:13.490 align:middle line:90%
as a pin.

00:18:13.490 --> 00:18:15.130 align:middle line:84%
He didn't normally
live like that.

00:18:15.130 --> 00:18:17.450 align:middle line:84%
His bed was made,
dishes were done.

00:18:17.450 --> 00:18:19.590 align:middle line:84%
Everything was in
perfect order for them

00:18:19.590 --> 00:18:20.882 align:middle line:90%
to come in after his departure.

00:18:20.882 --> 00:18:22.007 align:middle line:90%
>> GIESEMANN: That's right.

