in a strategic meeting.

00:28:15.380 --> 00:28:17.573 align:middle line:84%
How do we approach
this situation?

00:28:17.573 --> 00:28:19.240 align:middle line:84%
And there's no room
for that now, right?

00:28:19.240 --> 00:28:21.700 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN:
There's no room, no.

00:28:21.700 --> 00:28:23.260 align:middle line:84%
But it's interesting
because I just

00:28:23.260 --> 00:28:25.060 align:middle line:84%
had an experience the
other day of somebody

00:28:25.060 --> 00:28:26.840 align:middle line:84%
sent me-- we call
them in the Navy

00:28:26.840 --> 00:28:31.120 align:middle line:84%
a nastygram, an email
that was very nasty to me.

00:28:31.120 --> 00:28:34.460 align:middle line:84%
And luckily I can only think of
five of these over the years.

00:28:34.460 --> 00:28:36.200 align:middle line:84%
And immediately
you go like this,

00:28:36.200 --> 00:28:39.040 align:middle line:84%
but I've learned that
the ego does this

00:28:39.040 --> 00:28:41.560 align:middle line:90%
but the soul has no defenses.

00:28:41.560 --> 00:28:46.060 align:middle line:84%
And instead of deleting it,
I just wrote, I hear you.

00:28:46.060 --> 00:28:47.740 align:middle line:10%
I appreciate what you say.

00:28:47.740 --> 00:28:53.180 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps if you understood that
this is why this happened,

00:28:53.180 --> 00:28:55.620 align:middle line:90%
but may I offer you this?

00:28:55.620 --> 00:28:57.420 align:middle line:84%
Just like every
other time I've done

00:28:57.420 --> 00:29:01.360 align:middle line:84%
that, the person comes back with
capital letters, I'm so sorry.

00:29:01.360 --> 00:29:03.180 align:middle line:90%
I was so nasty.

00:29:03.180 --> 00:29:05.120 align:middle line:90%
Oh, my gosh, you heard me.

00:29:05.120 --> 00:29:07.260 align:middle line:84%
Can you imagine if we
brought that energy

00:29:07.260 --> 00:29:13.340 align:middle line:84%
into war rooms or boardrooms or
family living rooms, I hear you.

00:29:13.340 --> 00:29:15.580 align:middle line:84%
Let me see from
your perspective.

00:29:15.580 --> 00:29:17.040 align:middle line:90%
Can you see from mine?

00:29:17.040 --> 00:29:20.340 align:middle line:84%
With no defensiveness,
that's what's missing.

00:29:20.340 --> 00:29:24.640 align:middle line:84%
We're in our human mode, and
the brain, the left brain

00:29:24.640 --> 00:29:27.720 align:middle line:90%
is wired for self-defense.

00:29:27.720 --> 00:29:31.650 align:middle line:84%
So when you live with that
right brain balance more,

00:29:31.650 --> 00:29:34.400 align:middle line:84%
you automatically
go to alternatives

00:29:34.400 --> 00:29:36.600 align:middle line:84%
but are still aware
of the human mode.

00:29:36.600 --> 00:29:40.080 align:middle line:84%
>> ORTIZ: And beyond your
response to those emails,

00:29:40.080 --> 00:29:42.800 align:middle line:84%
you also have one of your
favorite phrases which is,

00:29:42.800 --> 00:29:44.340 align:middle line:90%
isn't that interesting?

00:29:44.340 --> 00:29:46.680 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: Oh yeah, that's
the first response always.

00:29:46.680 --> 00:29:50.460 align:middle line:84%
You look at that email and,
[GASPS] isn't that interesting?

00:29:50.460 --> 00:29:52.710 align:middle line:84%
That takes you
immediately to neutral.

00:29:52.710 --> 00:29:55.260 align:middle line:84%
>> ORTIZ: Yeah, it puts you
into the observer mindset.

00:29:55.260 --> 00:29:56.060 align:middle line:90%
>> GIESEMANN: Yeah.

00:29:56.060 --> 00:29:58.483 align:middle line:84%
We have people with t-shirts
on it now that say, isn't--

00:29:58.483 --> 00:29:59.900 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Isn't
that interesting?

00:29:59.900 --> 00:30:03.000 align:middle line:84%
Interesting is an
interesting word.

00:30:03.000 --> 00:30:06.200 align:middle line:84%
And so we, from
the ground up, are

00:30:06.200 --> 00:30:09.120 align:middle line:84%
starting to understand the
need to inculcate intelligence

00:30:09.120 --> 00:30:11.600 align:middle line:84%
into the heart and
operate through that,

00:30:11.600 --> 00:30:13.660 align:middle line:84%
so it's going to be
a ground-up thing.

00:30:13.660 --> 00:30:16.640 align:middle line:84%
They're the last-- they'll
be the last to get it, right?

00:30:16.640 --> 00:30:19.960 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: That's why I'm so
pleased that Wolf's messages,

00:30:19.960 --> 00:30:24.300 align:middle line:84%
the film and my book, is gaining
traction because people watch it

00:30:24.300 --> 00:30:25.820 align:middle line:90%
and it speaks to the heart.

00:30:25.820 --> 00:30:27.660 align:middle line:84%
There's a transmission
in there that people

00:30:27.660 --> 00:30:30.860 align:middle line:84%
can't not listen and
feel the emotion,

00:30:30.860 --> 00:30:33.820 align:middle line:90%
and it makes them think.

00:30:33.820 --> 00:30:36.590 align:middle line:84%
So we're balancing thinking
with the heart all of a sudden,

00:30:36.590 --> 00:30:37.590 align:middle line:90%
and it shifts something.

00:30:37.590 --> 00:30:38.465 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Oh it did.

00:30:38.465 --> 00:30:41.580 align:middle line:84%
I watched it this morning before
coming in here to the studio,

00:30:41.580 --> 00:30:43.800 align:middle line:90%
and I couldn't pull myself out.

00:30:43.800 --> 00:30:46.460 align:middle line:84%
I was in that energy,
and it took a while

00:30:46.460 --> 00:30:48.900 align:middle line:84%
to find my way back out of it
so I could sit here and chat

00:30:48.900 --> 00:30:50.820 align:middle line:90%
with both of you.

00:30:50.820 --> 00:30:53.593 align:middle line:84%
So I really encourage
people to watch it.

00:30:53.593 --> 00:30:55.980 align:middle line:84%
It's not just touching,
it's very empowering.

00:30:55.980 --> 00:30:58.800 align:middle line:84%
>> ORTIZ: He actually left a
whole scavenger hunt for you.

00:30:58.800 --> 00:30:59.600 align:middle line:90%
>> GIESEMANN: Yeah.

00:30:59.600 --> 00:31:01.400 align:middle line:84%
>> ORTIZ: And I'm
curious to know,

00:31:01.400 --> 00:31:04.460 align:middle line:84%
is there a mystery that
Wolf left behind that you

00:31:04.460 --> 00:31:06.200 align:middle line:90%
haven't been able to solve yet?

00:31:06.200 --> 00:31:09.160 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: I don't know
but there was one that I

00:31:09.160 --> 00:31:13.560 align:middle line:84%
didn't realize was unsolved that
became apparent when the film

00:31:13.560 --> 00:31:14.440 align:middle line:90%
came out.

00:31:14.440 --> 00:31:17.560 align:middle line:84%
Our Director, Jim
Spruell, found an ending

00:31:17.560 --> 00:31:19.580 align:middle line:84%
to this film that's
different from my book

00:31:19.580 --> 00:31:21.800 align:middle line:84%
because it hadn't happened
when I wrote the book.

00:31:21.800 --> 00:31:24.997 align:middle line:84%
And it has to do with the fact
that Wolf's stepmother, Beth, is

00:31:24.997 --> 00:31:27.080 align:middle line:84%
going through a tremendous
challenge with leukemia

00:31:27.080 --> 00:31:29.610 align:middle line:84%
right now and facing
her own death.

00:31:29.610 --> 00:31:30.410 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:31:30.410 --> 00:31:32.680 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: But I didn't
realize that if you watch

00:31:32.680 --> 00:31:34.860 align:middle line:84%
the film, there was
a book that moved.

00:31:34.860 --> 00:31:36.740 align:middle line:90%
I saw it move on the bookshelf.

00:31:36.740 --> 00:31:38.700 align:middle line:84%
Other people might say
it was a hallucination,

00:31:38.700 --> 00:31:41.080 align:middle line:84%
but that book said
to me, by moving,

00:31:41.080 --> 00:31:42.500 align:middle line:90%
you're supposed to buy this.

00:31:42.500 --> 00:31:45.320 align:middle line:84%
And there's a funny part in the
movie where it solved a mystery

00:31:45.320 --> 00:31:47.140 align:middle line:90%
from his original visit.

00:31:47.140 --> 00:31:50.680 align:middle line:10%
But there was another thing
in the book, a winged creature

00:31:50.680 --> 00:31:53.220 align:middle line:10%
that when I read the book
and looked at the picture,

00:31:53.220 --> 00:31:54.380 align:middle line:10%
Wolf dropped in on me.

00:31:54.380 --> 00:31:57.880 align:middle line:10%
It's in my book, Wolf's Message,
where I say, Wolf is here.

00:31:57.880 --> 00:31:59.640 align:middle line:10%
I wrote to his dad
and said, he tells me

00:31:59.640 --> 00:32:01.620 align:middle line:10%
he has a picture of
this winged creature.

00:32:01.620 --> 00:32:02.680 align:middle line:10%
Send it to me.

00:32:02.680 --> 00:32:03.740 align:middle line:90%
There was no question.

00:32:03.740 --> 00:32:06.670 align:middle line:84%
I didn't say, Mike, did he draw
a winged creature like this?

00:32:06.670 --> 00:32:07.470 align:middle line:90%
Wolf was here.

00:32:07.470 --> 00:32:09.310 align:middle line:84%
He said, have my
dad send you this.

00:32:09.310 --> 00:32:11.310 align:middle line:90%
Mike sent me Wolf's drawing.

00:32:11.310 --> 00:32:13.850 align:middle line:84%
It's identical to
what's in the book.

00:32:13.850 --> 00:32:15.690 align:middle line:90%
So, wow, that's really cool.

00:32:15.690 --> 00:32:17.170 align:middle line:90%
But why?

00:32:17.170 --> 00:32:18.150 align:middle line:90%
That was the point.

00:32:18.150 --> 00:32:20.090 align:middle line:90%
That was the mystery.

00:32:20.090 --> 00:32:22.930 align:middle line:84%
Well, that figure,
according to the book,

00:32:22.930 --> 00:32:25.090 align:middle line:84%
was called a chimera
where you cross

00:32:25.090 --> 00:32:28.970 align:middle line:84%
a DNA of an animal with
a human being, a chimera.

00:32:28.970 --> 00:32:31.710 align:middle line:84%
Well, just a few months
ago, Beth, Will's stepmother

00:32:31.710 --> 00:32:33.210 align:middle line:84%
who's going through
cancer treatment

00:32:33.210 --> 00:32:36.570 align:middle line:84%
and had a stem cell
transplant, texted me.

00:32:36.570 --> 00:32:39.290 align:middle line:84%
And she said, my
test results are in.

00:32:39.290 --> 00:32:43.510 align:middle line:84%
The donor's DNA is 100%
accepted by my body.

00:32:43.510 --> 00:32:46.560 align:middle line:90%
The chimerism test proved it.

00:32:46.560 --> 00:32:47.490 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Wow.

00:32:47.490 --> 00:32:51.970 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: And I gasped
because I saw this is a soul

00:32:51.970 --> 00:32:53.190 align:middle line:90%
thing.

00:32:53.190 --> 00:32:58.610 align:middle line:84%
Beth's soul agreed to
take on this illness

00:32:58.610 --> 00:33:02.770 align:middle line:84%
because the final bits of
the movie are so touching.

00:33:02.770 --> 00:33:04.710 align:middle line:84%
And the message that
we couldn't have

00:33:04.710 --> 00:33:08.030 align:middle line:84%
told if somebody had produced
this even five years earlier was

00:33:08.030 --> 00:33:12.210 align:middle line:84%
it takes away the fear
of death to know this,

00:33:12.210 --> 00:33:14.510 align:middle line:90%
that we are eternal souls.

00:33:14.510 --> 00:33:17.990 align:middle line:84%
And now I know why he
drew me to this chimera

00:33:17.990 --> 00:33:21.515 align:middle line:84%
back then, because just
you put the dots together.

00:33:21.515 --> 00:33:23.640 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: --things to
reveal themselves sometimes.

00:33:23.640 --> 00:33:24.840 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: There's
no time across the veil.

00:33:24.840 --> 00:33:27.380 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Treasure hunts
like that can take a lifetime.

00:33:27.380 --> 00:33:28.180 align:middle line:90%
It's beautiful.

00:33:28.180 --> 00:33:30.330 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: It's fun
to connect the dots.

00:33:30.330 --> 00:33:33.350 align:middle line:84%
But to connect that one
and say, Jim Spruell

00:33:33.350 --> 00:33:36.070 align:middle line:84%
knew to put that in there
because his soul and his son

00:33:36.070 --> 00:33:40.280 align:middle line:84%
across the veil guided him to
do that, it was perfection.

00:33:40.280 --> 00:33:43.910 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So we touched on but
didn't go into the soul group

00:33:43.910 --> 00:33:46.790 align:middle line:84%
that you talk with, Sanaya, so
let's talk about them a little

00:33:46.790 --> 00:33:48.610 align:middle line:90%
bit, what you do with them.

00:33:48.610 --> 00:33:50.270 align:middle line:84%
And right now is a
good time to start

00:33:50.270 --> 00:33:54.070 align:middle line:84%
sharing some of their messages
that come through repeatedly

00:33:54.070 --> 00:33:55.960 align:middle line:84%
for humanity at
this point in time.

00:33:55.960 --> 00:33:58.810 align:middle line:10%
>> GIESEMANN: Sanaya came to
me on my birthday in 2010.

00:33:58.810 --> 00:34:01.370 align:middle line:84%
In the film I say cool things
have happened on my birthday.

00:34:01.370 --> 00:34:02.810 align:middle line:84%
And one of them I
didn't reveal is

00:34:02.810 --> 00:34:05.670 align:middle line:84%
my guide, Sanaya, revealed
themselves to me on my birthday.

00:34:05.670 --> 00:34:07.310 align:middle line:90%
A very powerful group.

00:34:07.310 --> 00:34:08.810 align:middle line:90%
I said, who are you?

00:34:08.810 --> 00:34:12.010 align:middle line:84%
They said, we are a collective
consciousness of your guides.

00:34:12.010 --> 00:34:14.310 align:middle line:84%
And you will write and
write and write as us.

00:34:14.310 --> 00:34:17.270 align:middle line:84%
But I did not expect to
also be speaking as them.

00:34:17.270 --> 00:34:19.690 align:middle line:84%
It was very awkward
for this navy commander

00:34:19.690 --> 00:34:23.270 align:middle line:84%
to start channeling for a small
group, and now for large groups.

00:34:23.270 --> 00:34:25.010 align:middle line:84%
I've channeled for
up to 500 people.

00:34:25.010 --> 00:34:28.010 align:middle line:84%
And had a great conversation
with Lee Harris on my podcast

00:34:28.010 --> 00:34:29.750 align:middle line:84%
recently about the
book you did with him.

00:34:29.750 --> 00:34:31.770 align:middle line:84%
And it was fun to have
two channelers talking

00:34:31.770 --> 00:34:36.090 align:middle line:84%
together and comparing stories
and very, very similar.

00:34:36.090 --> 00:34:38.469 align:middle line:84%
It's a little awkward,
but you can't not do it.

00:34:38.469 --> 00:34:41.330 align:middle line:84%
We've had physical healings
from people in attendance

00:34:41.330 --> 00:34:44.010 align:middle line:84%
when the guides come through
because the energy is

00:34:44.010 --> 00:34:45.010 align:middle line:90%
so powerful.

00:34:45.010 --> 00:34:46.469 align:middle line:84%
And they're talking
through me now.

00:34:46.469 --> 00:34:51.010 align:middle line:84%
I always hook into them before
I do an interview because they

00:34:51.010 --> 00:34:53.250 align:middle line:84%
have the bigger picture,
and their answers

00:34:53.250 --> 00:34:56.237 align:middle line:84%
are going to be much wiser than
anything I could come up with.

00:34:56.237 --> 00:34:58.570 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So what are some
specifics they're telling us

00:34:58.570 --> 00:35:02.260 align:middle line:84%
now, as humanity, that we need
to start really keying into?

00:35:02.260 --> 00:35:05.790 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: They
say to watch the fear,

00:35:05.790 --> 00:35:10.170 align:middle line:84%
that these times really are not
that much worse than they were

00:35:10.170 --> 00:35:10.970 align:middle line:90%
in the past.

00:35:10.970 --> 00:35:13.030 align:middle line:84%
It only seems that
way, especially

00:35:13.030 --> 00:35:15.930 align:middle line:84%
because the media is
putting it in our face.

00:35:15.930 --> 00:35:20.750 align:middle line:84%
And we are falling right into
the trap of giving that more

00:35:20.750 --> 00:35:25.030 align:middle line:84%
intention than the underlying
things, the slower things

00:35:25.030 --> 00:35:27.510 align:middle line:84%
that we need to be
paying attention to.

00:35:27.510 --> 00:35:29.490 align:middle line:90%
How are we treating each other?

00:35:29.490 --> 00:35:33.070 align:middle line:84%
Why are we allowing people
to mistreat each other

00:35:33.070 --> 00:35:36.770 align:middle line:84%
and violence that we
just take for granted,

00:35:36.770 --> 00:35:40.730 align:middle line:84%
and violent movies
and poor food choices,

00:35:40.730 --> 00:35:44.710 align:middle line:84%
everything that leads to
illness and the underlying

00:35:44.710 --> 00:35:49.070 align:middle line:84%
causes for the big change,
things that make the news.

00:35:49.070 --> 00:35:53.350 align:middle line:84%
So they're saying, watch
the fear, be present now.

00:35:53.350 --> 00:35:55.790 align:middle line:84%
Listen to the
guidance within and

00:35:55.790 --> 00:35:59.752 align:middle line:84%
flow, which is Wolf
spelled out backwards.

00:35:59.752 --> 00:36:01.180 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: That's
right, the flow.

00:36:01.180 --> 00:36:01.980 align:middle line:90%
>> ORTIZ: OK.

00:36:01.980 --> 00:36:02.780 align:middle line:90%
>> GIESEMANN: Yeah.

00:36:02.780 --> 00:36:06.520 align:middle line:84%
>> ORTIZ: I think a lot of it is
we ignore that there's this true

00:36:06.520 --> 00:36:09.460 align:middle line:84%
self that you say is
not just the spirit,

00:36:09.460 --> 00:36:13.200 align:middle line:84%
it's not just the physical,
but it's a merge between both.

00:36:13.200 --> 00:36:15.320 align:middle line:84%
Instead of just knowing
that intellectually

00:36:15.320 --> 00:36:20.440 align:middle line:84%
that we have a true self, how
do you live in daily harmony

00:36:20.440 --> 00:36:21.590 align:middle line:90%
with your true self?

00:36:21.590 --> 00:36:23.340 align:middle line:84%
>> GIESEMANN: In my
book The Awakened Way,

00:36:23.340 --> 00:36:25.760 align:middle line:84%
I talk about having
a miracle mindset.

00:36:25.760 --> 00:36:28.280 align:middle line:84%
We really need to come to know
that this true self is not

00:36:28.280 --> 00:36:30.060 align:middle line:90%
just a concept we talk about.

00:36:30.060 --> 00:36:33.400 align:middle line:84%
It really is the source
of all these wonders.

00:36:33.400 --> 00:36:35.760 align:middle line:90%
So you can sit quietly and say--

00:36:35.760 --> 00:36:41.400 align:middle line:84%
I literally say bring on
the miracles, bring it on.

00:36:41.400 --> 00:36:43.640 align:middle line:84%
And that has to come
from the deepest place

00:36:43.640 --> 00:36:46.160 align:middle line:90%
where anything is possible.

00:36:46.160 --> 00:36:47.940 align:middle line:90%
And it will happen.

00:36:47.940 --> 00:36:49.800 align:middle line:90%
Miracles become the norm.

00:36:49.800 --> 00:36:52.460 align:middle line:84%
And then you have to say,
well, how did that happen?

00:36:52.460 --> 00:36:54.680 align:middle line:90%
How did you explain that?

00:36:54.680 --> 00:36:58.980 align:middle line:10%
So ask to have what I call
NOEs, no other explanation

00:36:58.980 --> 00:37:02.420 align:middle line:10%
moments, and then,
hopefully, by grace, you'll

00:37:02.420 --> 00:37:05.880 align:middle line:10%
have this moment where
you say there is a God,

00:37:05.880 --> 00:37:07.820 align:middle line:10%
but it's not some being.

00:37:07.820 --> 00:37:14.740 align:middle line:84%
It's this being itself that
just has to create miracles

00:37:14.740 --> 00:37:16.460 align:middle line:90%
to get our attention.

00:37:16.460 --> 00:37:20.860 align:middle line:84%
So it's a process of changing
your whole understanding of what

00:37:20.860 --> 00:37:26.500 align:middle line:84%
God is to it's this bigger
self that's breathing us.

00:37:26.500 --> 00:37:27.840 align:middle line:90%
See, I never talked like this.

00:37:27.840 --> 00:37:29.980 align:middle line:84%
I never had that
realization when I first

00:37:29.980 --> 00:37:30.923 align:middle line:90%
started as a medium.

00:37:30.923 --> 00:37:32.340 align:middle line:84%
For me it was just
let me show you

00:37:32.340 --> 00:37:34.460 align:middle line:84%
your loved ones
haven't really died.

00:37:34.460 --> 00:37:38.860 align:middle line:84%
But it has opened up
this sacred awareness

00:37:38.860 --> 00:37:43.686 align:middle line:84%
of what is the true self
that's called self-realization.

00:37:43.686 --> 00:37:47.423 align:middle line:84%
